    {
      "topic": "What is this?",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "<p>This is a collection of language specific resources that can be used to look up the best practices followed by a particular language's community.</p>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "topic": "Why does this repo exist?",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "<p>I dabble into multiple programming languages and I wanted to have a central place that I can refer to whenever I am looking up best practices for a particular language.</p>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "topic": "What counts as an acceptable entry?",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "<p>It could be anything from articles to books to videos that describes:</p>"
        },
        {
          "title": "how to write idiomatic code in a particular language"
        },
        {
          "title": "what build systems / package managers to use and the best practices surrounding these aforementioned tools"
        },
        {
          "title": "how to good write unit/integration tests"
        },
        {
          "title": "different styles, design patterns &amp; idioms of a language"
        },
        {
          "title": "new language section (if you find that the resources for your favourite language are missing feel free to create a new section and add them)<p><strong>Note:</strong> If you are adding a book to the list make sure that it is a free ebook. Amazon links to buy books will not be accepted.</p>"
        }
      ]
    },
